{
  "texts": [
    "The current hype about generative AI's capabilities touts productivity by reassigning routine mental tasks of workers to machines [129].",
    "McKinsey predicts that, if AI delivers on this promise, there is the potential to automate work activities that absorb 60-70 percent of employees' time today (ibid.).",
    "Such statements create a sense of a new technology \"silver bullet\" in the competitive scramble to continuously cut costs in business leaders' planning priorities and resulting technology investments.",
    "Businesses acting on this promise of productivity via generative AI technologies would result in a dramatic reduction in person-hours, and, if existing employees are not deliberately redeployed to other productive work, a drastic loss of jobs [17,130].",
    "This category of job loss will include those that have the most administrative or repetitive elements, like clerical or customer service work on the lower end of the wage scale and therefore widens the economic gap brought about by the shrinking of the middle class (ibid.)."
  ]
}